THOUGHT: The miscompile happens when InstCombine folds select driven by fcmp into fabs without considering NaNs. We previously disabled the entire fold, causing tests to fail. A targeted fix is to implement a minimal, safe fold inside foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs: only perform the transformation when the select has nnan and its arms are of the form (-X, X) or (X, -X). This preserves behavior for NaNs and satisfies existing tests that expect the nnan fold. I will replace the function body to:
- Bail out unless SI.hasNoNaNs().
- Detect select arms patterns (-X, X) or (X, -X).
- Replace with llvm.fabs(X) accordingly.

```bash
python3 - <<'PY'
import re, pathlib
p = pathlib.Path("llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp")
s = p.read_text()

pat = re.compile(r'(Instruction\s*\*\s*foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs\s*\(\s*SelectInst\s*&\s*SI\s*,\s*InstCombinerImpl\s*&\s*IC\s*\)\s*\{)', re.S)
m = pat.search(s)
if not m:
    print("Function signature not found.")
else:
    start = m.end()
    # find end of function by brace matching
    depth = 1
    i = start
    while i < len(s) and depth > 0:
        if s[i] == '{':
            depth += 1
        elif s[i] == '}':
            depth -= 1
        i += 1
    body = r"""
  // Minimal safe fold: only when nnan is set and arms are -X and X.
  if (!SI.hasNoNaNs())
    return nullptr;

  Value *TrueVal = SI.getTrueValue();
  Value *FalseVal = SI.getFalseValue();

  Value *X = nullptr;
  // Case: select Cond, -X, X --> fabs(X)
  if (match(TrueVal, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && X == FalseVal) {
    Value *Fabs = IC.Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, &SI);
    return IC.replaceInstUsesWith(SI, Fabs);
  }
  X = nullptr;
  // Case: select Cond, X, -X --> fabs(X)
  if (match(FalseVal, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && X == TrueVal) {
    Value *Fabs = IC.Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, &SI);
    return IC.replaceInstUsesWith(SI, Fabs);
  }

  return nullptr;
"""
    s = s[:start] + body + s[i-1:]
    p.write_text(s)
    print("Updated foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs with nnan guard and minimal (-X,X)/(X,-X) fabs fold.")
PY
```

